90
00:07:45,148 --> 00:07:47,410
The characters of Splatoon are squids that can transform to become humanoids.

91
00:08:09,915 --> 00:08:13,197
At first, we were surprised that the main character was a squid,

92
00:08:13,277 --> 00:08:16,620
but there was a reason for the creation of this character,

93
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:18,701
and until it was born, there were many theories.

94
00:08:19,662 --> 00:08:24,305
People are often surprised when they first hear that the main character for our game is a squid,

95
00:08:24,825 --> 00:08:27,127
but there are reasons why things ended up this way,

96
00:08:27,447 --> 00:08:31,630
and the road leading to the character's final design was not without its twists and turns.

97
00:08:38,638 --> 00:08:49,364
As development progressed from prototyping to creating an actual product, the characters we first relied on were rabbits.

98
00:08:51,585 --> 00:08:57,968
Rabbits have different colors, such as black and white, which are suitable for the Chinese character.

99
00:08:57,988 --> 00:09:00,109
It is also said that rabbits have a strong sense of balance.

100
00:09:01,239 --> 00:09:05,301
Rabbits can be both black and white, making them easy to separate into teams.

101
00:09:05,861 --> 00:09:09,442
We also learned that rabbits are apparently very territorial creatures.

102
00:09:11,243 --> 00:09:17,346
We wanted to use brightly colored inks and thought they would contrast well with the neutral color of the rabbits.

103
00:09:18,706 --> 00:09:24,428
We wanted to use brightly colored inks and thought they would contrast well with the neutral color of the rabbits.

104
00:09:26,109 --> 00:09:29,871
We were able to explain some of the reasons why we chose rabbits as characters.

105
00:09:31,392 --> 00:09:35,717
These were all reasons we could use to explain why we'd gone with rabbits as characters.

106
00:09:50,038 --> 00:09:52,080
But what would rabbits be doing shooting ink?

107
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:56,102
Why would rabbits be able to submerge themselves in the ink once they shot it?

108
00:09:56,923 --> 00:10:01,245
These were the sorts of questions that came up when I showed our game to others in the company.

109
00:10:02,566 --> 00:10:04,607
I think it was a lack of persuasion.

110
00:10:05,728 --> 00:10:07,829
Something about the concept still didn't sit right.

111
00:10:07,849 --> 00:10:12,692
I felt that this was not just a mistake in the way the characters were chosen,

112
00:10:12,712 --> 00:10:16,955
but that there was a part of the game's idea that was not sufficiently integrated.

113
00:10:18,749 --> 00:10:21,050
So I thought that the game's appearance and gameplay didn't match.

114
00:10:21,070 --> 00:10:22,090
To solve this problem, Sakaguchi, the director,

115
00:10:22,110 --> 00:10:22,990
organized the player's performance.

116
00:10:45,082 --> 00:10:49,424
To help tackle this problem, one of Splatoon's directors, Mr. Sakaguchi,

117
00:10:50,245 --> 00:10:53,106
organized and consolidated what the player's abilities would be.

118
00:10:53,126 --> 00:10:56,388
When not submerged in ink, you would be able to attack.

119
00:10:56,408 --> 00:10:59,650
While submerged in ink, you would lose that ability to attack,

120
00:10:59,670 --> 00:11:01,611
but would recover health and could move more quickly.

121
00:11:18,181 --> 00:11:22,264
We distributed player abilities across two different forms that the player could take,

122
00:11:22,724 --> 00:11:24,385
each with their own pros and cons.

123
00:11:35,605 --> 00:11:38,087
We had all sorts of different character design ideas.

124
00:11:38,888 --> 00:11:41,330
And squids were actually one of the original candidates,

125
00:11:41,730 --> 00:11:43,592
but we couldn't find a definitive reason

126
00:11:43,652 --> 00:11:45,374
to choose one design over another.

127
00:11:45,394 --> 00:11:50,958
But once we thought of this ability to move quickly

128
00:11:51,318 --> 00:11:53,841
through ink as swimming, we discovered a strong reason

129
00:11:53,861 --> 00:11:55,302
to go with squids as our characters.

130
00:12:15,225 --> 00:12:20,189
And to further distinguish between these two ability states, we decided to have the character

131
00:12:20,269 --> 00:12:22,992
take on a more humanoid appearance when not submerged in ink.

132
00:12:23,072 --> 00:12:27,596
And so our characters were born, squids that can transform into people.

133
00:12:34,873 --> 00:12:36,275
This also solidified another pillar of Splatoon's gameplay,

134
00:12:36,315 --> 00:12:38,316
that battles would unfold with characters switching back and forth between these two forms.

135
00:12:38,336 --> 00:12:40,378
We discovered that the act of solving problems in this way gave birth to new gameplay ideas.

136
